<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to subg. 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Stachygynandrum)" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stachygynandrum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Stachygynandrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is characterized by its erect habit, stoloniferous stems, leaves seemingly monomorphic below first branch, and median leaves acuminate to aristate, ciliate, and broadly hyaline. 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella fragillima" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="fragillima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella fragillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a poorly known taxon that 
<bibRefCitation author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B1" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany 9 (4): 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
maintained as a distinct species. Our examination of type material of 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella fragillima" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="fragillima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella fragillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
causes us to conclude that it is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, under which it is synonymized here. See comparison of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valdespino, G. Heringer &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2015" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella sematophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="sematophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella sematophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under the latter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B1" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany 9 (4): 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Ule 7298</emphasis>
(B!, BM!) from Bahia and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Glaziou 11723</emphasis>
(BM!, P-image!, US!) from Rio de Janeiro as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Ule 7298</emphasis>
is here assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valdespino" authorityYear="2015" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella blepharodella" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="blepharodella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella blepharodella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Glaziou 11723</emphasis>
morphologically does not fit 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; therefore, we exclude Bahia and Rio de Janeiro from the range of the latter species. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vestiens" order="Selaginellales" pageId="22" pageNumber="83" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vestiens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="83">Selaginella vestiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here cited and those cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Heringer, G" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Ciencias Biologicas da Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais, Belo Horizonte" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 98" refId="B6" refString="Heringer, G, 2011. Selaginellaceae Willk. no estado de Minas Gerais, Brasil. Instituto de Ciencias Biologicas da Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais, Belo Horizonte: 1 - 98" title="Selaginellaceae Willk. no estado de Minas Gerais, Brasil" year="2011">Heringer (2011)</bibRefCitation>
are either from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
(i.e., type collection) or from Minas Gerais in Brazil.
</paragraph>
